<TITLE> Advisers sit with CPB, Workers Party </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com)Four advisers to the caretaker government met with the Communist Party of Bangladesh and the Workers Party of Bangladesh Monday, as part of ongoing sessions meant to prepare for forthcoming formal dialogue between the government and political parties. The meeting with CPB, starting at noon and ending at 12.45 pm, took place at state guest house Meghna. The party's central committee member Ahsan Habib Lablu told bdnews24.com that acting president Shahidullah Chowdhury, general secretary Mujahidul Islam Selim, Lablu and fellow central committee members Morshed Ali and Ruhin Hossain Prince were attending Monday's meeting at the invitation of an adviser. Foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury, communications adviser Ghulam Quader, LGRD adviser Anwarul Iqbal and commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman later sat with representatives of the Workers Party around 1.00 pm. General secretary Bimal Biswas told bdnews24.com that he was representing his party alongside politburo members Haider Akbar Khan Rono, Fazle Hossain Badshah, Anisur Rahman Mallick and Quamrul Ahsan. Advisers have so far held informal talks with Awami League, Jatiya Party, the reformist faction of BNP and Jamaat-e-Islami. They are set to hold another meeting with Islami Oikyo Jote Monday night. IOJ chairman Mufti Fazlul Haque Amini said the meeting would be held at guest house Meghna at 8.00 pm. Amini will lead a 10-member delegation of the party. bdnews24
